ECON5540 | Industrial Organization and Regulations | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON5540 Industrial Organization and Regulations | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 554, ECON 613A] Industrial organization studies behavior of firms and industries, and their consequence in markets, mainly under imperfect competition. It also examines their implication for public policy including antitrust issues and industryregulations. This course is graduate level introduction of theoretical foundation and empirical techniques in industrial organization. Prerequisite(s): ECON 5130 or ECON 5210
ECON5550 | Advanced Topics in Economic Growth | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON5550 Advanced Topics in Economic Growth | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 6120F] This PhD course aims to address several topics that are active in the field of economic growth, including, but not limited to, (1) structural change, (2) firm and industry dynamics, (3) political economy, (4) international trade, (5) pertinent research about China's growth and development. Exclusion(s): ECON 6120F  Prerequisite(s): ECON 5250
ECON5560 | International Trade and Investment | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON5560 International Trade and Investment | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 6120G] This is an advanced course on the economics of international trade and foreign direct investment (FDI). In this course, students learn to analyze the causes and consequences of international trade and foreign direct investment. Topics include the sources of gains from trade, the determinants of trade pattern, offshoring, multinational production, geography & trade, and implications of trade policies. Exclusion(s): ECON 6120C, ECON 6120D, ECON 6120G  Prerequisite(s): ECON 5130 OR (ECON 5210 AND ECON 5220)
ECON5570 | Advanced Topics in Macroeconomics | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON5570 Advanced Topics in Macroeconomics | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 6120A] The objective of this course is to study the implications of financial market imperfections for macroeconomics and finance, including uninsurable idiosyncratic risks, asymmetric information, moral hazard, agency costs, adjustment costs, and taxation. Lecture is focused on the theoretical foundation of financial imperfections and their qualitative implications. Students need to present papers to the class and complete a computation/estimation project. Exclusion(s): ECON 6120A  Prerequisite(s): ECON 5250
ECON6100-6190 | Special Topics | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON6100-6190 Special Topics | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 610-619] Selected topics from the frontiers of research in economic theory and application.
ECON6950 | MSc Project | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON6950 MSc Project | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 695] An independent project carried out under the supervision of a faculty member. Prerequisite(s): MSc status
ECON6970 | Independent Study | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON6970 Independent Study | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 697] Study of selected economic issues under the supervision of a faculty member in the Department. (Special permission from the Associate Dean is required for MBA students to take this course.)
ECON6980 | Independent Project | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON6980 Independent Project | description:For MSc(ECON) students opting for the Research Preparation concentration only. This course aims to acquire students with research skills through producing a term paper under the supervision of a faculty member in the Department.
ECON6990 | MPhil Thesis Research | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON6990 MPhil Thesis Research | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 699] Master's thesis research supervised by a faculty member.  A successful defense of the thesis leads to the grade Pass.  No course credit is assigned.
ECON7800 | Economics Seminar | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON7800 Economics Seminar | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 780] Research seminars presented by students, faculty and guest speakers. Students are expected to attend regularly. May be repeated for credit.  Graded P or F.
ECON7900 | Doctoral Seminar | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON7900 Doctoral Seminar | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 790] Presentations and discussions of current research projects conducted by PhD students, faculty and visiting scholars. A required course of MPhil (ECON) and PhD (ECON) programs.
ECON7990 | Doctoral Thesis Research | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=ECON7990 Doctoral Thesis Research | description:[Previous Course Code(s): ECON 799] Original and independent doctoral thesis research.  A successful defense of the thesis leads to the grade Pass.  No course credit is assigned.
